topics.body:
"@Carcass Strife":/dis/the-time-wasting-thread/post/55a84bef6368726507002a95#post_55a84bef6368726507002a95

Each pokemon species has its own basic strengths and weaknesses, but how weak/strong a individual of said species is determined by a random mathematical code in the game that results in an "IV". To produce these IVs for yourself, though, you have one of two options - find 2 wild pokemon with 2 or 3 IVs in the wild from the "field" egg group (since it's one of the largest) and chain breed them until you get a baby pokemon with 4 or more IVs, or just breed with pokemon that already have IVs that you can get very easily from Wonder Trade. The latter is easier.
